					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Gotta turn off the screen at a safe time (like PPU clock 256-341), do your palette changes, set the VRAM address back to scroll properly, then turn the screen back on at a safe time.
<br />You see garbage in the overscan areas during mid-screen palette changes, highly visible in the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y306cWw98a4" class="postlink">Angry Video Game Nerd's review of Back to the Future</a>, and also visible in video captures of other NES games, such as <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-iKQIYK1AuI" class="postlink">Super Off Road</a>, or <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PM0jvj2GEgM" class="postlink">Fantastic Adventures of Dizzy</a></div>

